## Track 2: Chatbot Improvements (2–3 days)

### Current Chatbot Assessment

**What's Working Well:**
- ✅ ReAct agent loop with parallel tool execution
- ✅ Memory extraction pipeline (long-term user facts)
- ✅ Helicone observability integration
- ✅ Error classification (semantic vs system errors)
- ✅ 4 useful tools (fetch workouts, log food, search exercises, create templates)

**What Needs Improvement:**

| Issue | Impact | Priority |
|-------|--------|----------|
| No streaming — user waits for full response | Poor UX, feels slow | 🔴 High |
| No conversation persistence in DB | History resets on refresh | 🔴 High |
| System prompt is hardcoded, not versioned | Can't A/B test prompts | 🟡 Medium |
| No input guardrails (PII, off-topic, prompt injection) | Safety risk | 🟡 Medium |
| No output guardrails (hallucination, harmful advice) | Safety risk | 🟡 Medium |
| No token usage tracking per user | Can't manage costs | 🟡 Medium |
| Context always pulls ALL data (not the blueprint's selective retrieval) | Token waste | 🟠 Low-Med |
| No quick-prompt suggestions | UX enhancement | 🟢 Low |

### Improvements to Build

#### Phase A: Streaming Response (SSE)
- Add Server-Sent Events endpoint instead of waiting for full response
- Use Gemini SDK's `generateContentStream()` instead of `generateContent()`
- Frontend: parse SSE chunks and render incrementally

#### Phase B: Conversation Persistence
- Store conversations in DB (add `ai_conversations` table if not already in Prisma schema)
- Load history on chat open, paginate older messages
- This also enables evaluation later

#### Phase C: Guardrails
**Input guardrails** (before LLM call):
- Topic boundary: reject non-fitness queries ("write me a poem") with the system prompt
- Max message length: 500 chars
- Rate limit: 20 AI calls/user/hour

**Output guardrails** (after LLM call):
- Check for medical advice disclaimers when health-related
- Filter responses suggesting extreme caloric deficits (<1200 kcal)
- Regex-based PII leak detection on output

#### Phase D: Implement Selective Context Retrieval
The blueprint describes a full context engineering pipeline (intent classifier → context retriever → prompt assembler) that's not yet implemented. Currently [buildUserContext](file:///Users/ravichandu/Documents/Job%20Hunt%20-%2026/Projects/vital-sync/server/src/services/ai/prompts.ts#6-77) always pulls everything. Consider implementing the keyword-based intent classifier from the blueprint.

