## Track 3: AWS Bedrock Migration + Credit System (3–4 days)

### Why Bedrock?
| Gemini Free Tier | AWS Bedrock |
|-----------------|-------------|
| Hard rate limits (15 RPM, 1M TPM) | Pay-per-use, no hard limits |
| Free but unreliable for production | Enterprise-grade SLA |
| Single provider lock-in | Access to Claude, Llama, Mistral, Titan |
| No fine-tuning | Fine-tuning available |

### What to Learn
- **AWS Bedrock SDK** (`@aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime`): `InvokeModel` and `InvokeModelWithResponseStream`
- **IAM roles** for Bedrock access (your ECS task role already exists from deployment)
- **Model IDs**: `anthropic.claude-3-haiku-20240307`, `anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022`, etc.
- **Token counting** and pricing per model

### Architecture: LLM Abstraction Layer

Create a provider-agnostic LLM service so you can swap providers:

```typescript
// server/src/services/llm/provider.ts
interface LLMProvider {
  chat(params: ChatParams): Promise<string>;
  chatStream(params: ChatParams): AsyncGenerator<string>;
  countTokens(text: string): Promise<number>;
}

// Implementations:
// - GeminiProvider (current, keep for local dev)
// - BedrockProvider (production)
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tool calling migration**: Gemini's tool calling format differs from Bedrock/Claude's. You'll need to translate the tool definitions and function call responses between formats. This is the trickiest part of the migration.

### Credit System Design

#### Database Schema
```prisma
model UserCredits {
  id            String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId        String   @unique
  user          User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  totalCredits  Int      @default(100)   // initial free credits (in cents)
  usedCredits   Int      @default(0)
  maxCredits    Int      @default(500)   // hard cap per user
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt
}

model UsageLog {
  id            String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId        String
  model         String                    // "claude-3-haiku", "gemini-2.5-flash"
  inputTokens   Int
  outputTokens  Int
  costCents     Float                     // computed cost
  endpoint      String                    // "chat", "memory-extraction"
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
}
```

#### Flow
1. **Before LLM call**: check `usedCredits < totalCredits` → deny with 402 if exceeded
2. **After LLM call**: count tokens → compute cost → increment `usedCredits` → log to `UsageLog`
3. **API endpoint**: `GET /api/credits` → returns balance, usage, history
4. **Admin/Initial credits**: on signup, give 100 credits (~50 conversations with Haiku)

#### Pricing Reference (per 1M tokens)
| Model | Input | Output | ~Cost per chat turn |
|-------|-------|--------|-------------------|
| Claude 3 Haiku | $0.25 | $1.25 | ~$0.003 |
| Claude 3.5 Sonnet | $3.00 | $15.00 | ~$0.04 |
| Gemini 2.5 Flash | Free (for now) | Free | $0 |

### How This Works in Industry
- **OpenAI/Anthropic APIs**: strictly pay-per-token, pre-paid credits
- **Vercel AI**: per-message pricing with user-level caps
- **Most SaaS**: free tier (X messages/month) → paid tier → enterprise
- **Key principle**: always have a hard cap. Never let a single user run up unlimited costs.

