## Resources to Study

### Redis Caching
- [Redis Caching Patterns (official)](https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/use/client-side-caching/) — cache-aside, write-through, write-behind
- [Caching Best Practices (AWS)](https://aws.amazon.com/caching/best-practices/) — TTL strategies, invalidation

### AWS Bedrock
- [Bedrock Getting Started](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/getting-started.html)
- [Bedrock Runtime SDK for JS](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSJavaScriptSDK/v3/latest/client/bedrock-runtime/)
- [Converse API](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/conversation-inference.html) — unified API for all models including tool calling

### LLM Evaluation
- [promptfoo (open-source eval)](https://www.promptfoo.dev/) — eval runner, CI integration
- [LangSmith Docs](https://docs.smith.langchain.com/) — tracing, datasets, annotation
- [Hamel Husain's "Your AI Product Needs Evals"](https://hamel.dev/blog/posts/evals/) — best industry writeup on eval frameworks
- [Anthropic's Eval Guide](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/develop-tests) — gold standard for eval design

### Chatbot Best Practices
- [Anthropic's Prompt Engineering Guide](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering) — system prompts, guardrails
- [Vercel AI SDK](https://sdk.vercel.ai/) — streaming, tool calling abstraction (good reference architecture)
